Average interest rate spreads in the federal funds market. For each of the 164 institutions listed intable 2, the average interest rate spread relative to the effective federal funds rate was calculated using data from the first half of 1998. This figure plots the frequency distribution of this spread for the nine LTCM banks that participated in the hedge fund’s rescue, banks that were designated as large, complex banking organizations (LCBO banks) that did not ultimately participate in the LTCM rescue, and all other active market participants that are listed intable 2. Active participants are those that borrowed federal funds more than 75% of the days during the first half of 1998.
